  "prompt": "What to do when you don't want to do?",
  "response": "When you're struggling with motivation, here are some strategies to help:\n\n1. Break tasks into smaller, manageable steps\n- Start with the smallest possible action\n- Create a simple to-do list\n- Use the \"2-minute rule\"\n\n2. Use psychological techniques\n- Set a timer for 5-10 minutes and start\n- Promise yourself a reward after completing the task\n- Visualize the benefits of completing the task\n\n3. Address underlying issues\n- Check your energy levels and health\n- Ensure you're getting enough sleep\n- Evaluate potential burnout or depression\n\n4. Change your environment\n- Clean and organize your workspace\n- Remove distractions\n- Find a new location to work\n\n5. Motivation techniques\n- Use positive self-talk\n- Practice self-compassion\n- Listen to motivational podcasts or music\n\n6. Create accountability\n- Tell someone about your goals\n- Work with a partner or join a group\n- Use apps that track progress\n\n7. Practice mindfulness\n- Focus on the present moment\n- Use meditation or deep breathing\n- Accept your feelings without judgment\n\n8. Try the \"five-second rule\"\n- Count down from 5\n- Take action before your brain stops you\n\nRemember, motivation often follows action, not the other way around.",
